-- RWE Plans Additional Cost Cuts Under New CEO, Spiegel Reports
-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 2012-02-05T13:50:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/rwe-plans-additional-cost-cuts-under-new-ceo-spiegel-reports.html
RWE AG (RWE) ,  Germany ’s second-largest
utility, is planning additional cost cuts in 2013 and 2014 under
designated Chief Executive Officer Peter Terium,  Der Spiegel 
reported, citing a report for the Essen-based company’s workers’
representatives.  According to the report, Terium plans to reduce costs by at
least another 1 billion euros ($1.3 billion) on top of 1.5
billion euros of reductions already announced, the magazine
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Suess in Munich at 
